General.Name: Miramar Resources Ltd
General.Description: Miramar Resources Limited engages in the exploration and evaluation of mining tenements in Australia. The company primarily explores for gold, nickel, copper, and platinum group element deposits. It holds interests in three underexplored gold projects, including the Gidji JV, Glandore, and Randalls located within the Eastern Goldfields region near Kalgoorlie in Western Australia; two projects covering under-explored greenstone belts, such as the Lang Well and Lakeside in Murchison region; and two projects comprising the Whaleshark and Bangemall in Gascoyne region in Western Australia. The company was incorporated in 2019 and is based in South Perth, Australia.
